properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 8:50AM CST until January 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTRY MIX OF FREEZING DRIZZLE AND SNOW EXPECTED TODAY...

.Low pressure approaching from the Northern Plains will produce a
mixture of snow, light freezing rain and freezing drizzle across
northern and central Wisconsin. While snow and ice accumulations
are expected to be relatively light, driving conditions will
likely become hazardous in some areas. The threat of freezing
precipitation will taper off over central Wisconsin this afternoon
as temperatures warm above freezing.

* WHAT...A mix of light freezing rain, freezing drizzle and light
snow. Ice accumulation of less than one-tenth of an inch. Little
snow accumulation expected.

* WHERE...Menominee, Marathon and Shawano Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on icy road conditions. The hazardous conditions
could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Wisconsin can be obtained by
calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING
